This is a sample app for http://www.tropo.com/ that works with voice, SMS, IM and Twitter.

Read about how to set up Twitter support at Tropo.com in this blog post:

http://blog.tropo.com/2010/03/25/how-to-add-twitter-support-to-a-tropo-com-app-step-by-step/

The code is based on this python sample app:

https://www.tropo.com/docs/scripting/t_python-yahooweather.htm

But I've modified it so that the weather conditions all go back in a single tweet. I have
also modified it so that the voice channel gets different treatment from text channels.

My next step is to modify it so that it only asks for a ZIP code if one isn't provided.
